quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,17,"So, you did not kill them, but Allah killed them; and in no way did you (i.e., the prophet) throw when you threw, but Allah threw, and that He might try the believers by a fair trial from Himself. Surely Allah is Ever-Hearing, Ever-Knowing"
  8,18,That (The Arabic pronoun is in the plural form) is for you; and (know) that Allah is enfeebling the plotting of the disbelievers
  8,19,"In case you seek arbitration, then arbitration has already come to you; and in case you refrain, then it is a most charitable thing for you; and in case you go back, We will go back, and your community will never avail you anything, though it be many; and that Allah is with the believers"
  8,20,"O you who have believed, obey Allah and His Messenger and do not turn away from him, (even) as you hear (him speak)"
  8,21,"And do not be as the ones who have said, \"We hear, \" and they do not hear"
  8,22,"Surely the evilest of beasts in the Meeting with Allah are the deaf, the dumb, who do not consider"
  8,23,"And if Allah had known of any charity in them, indeed He would have made them hear; and if He had made them hear, they would have turned back (while) veering away from (His words)"
  8,24,"O you who have believed, respond to Allah and to the Messenger when He calls you to that which enlivens you; and know that Allah interposes between a person and his heart, and that to Him you will be mustered"
  8,25,And protect yourselves against a temptation which will definitely not afflict in particular the ones who did injustice among you; and that Allah is strict in punishment